Doc Del,<br><br>
We appreciate the time, and the effort, you are taking to communicate.  My wife is in the medical field (hospital pharmacy), and we know the tremendous effort it takes to come back after a problem such as yours.  I also know that you are not one to give up, and we are richer for your writing.  <br><br>
Keep up the good work, and enjoy your sunny weather in Hawaii.  It has rained here all day, and I was out pulling weeds out of the muck (it's easier that way).<br><br>
Now, we can look back on those experiences, see rainy days and days of bright sunshine, recount experiences, and learn from each other.  None of us knows when his or her last day upon this earth will be, and we all hope for long, productive lives.  That is my New Year's Wish for you, Doc Del, and the others on this site.  
